SIMPLE: brocket
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Brocket
<hw>Brock"et</hw> <pr>(br⟦ocr⟧k"⟦ecr⟧t)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>broket</ets>, F. <ets>broquart</ets> fallow deer a year old, fr.
the same root as E. <ets>broach</ets>, meaning point (hence tine of a
horn).]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A male red deer two
years old; -- sometimes called <altname>brock</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A small South American deer, of
several species (<spn>Coassus superciliaris</spn>, <spn>Coassus
rufus</spn>, and <spn>Coassus auritus</spn>).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Brockish</ent>⟦br⟧
